section: 12. Contributing
text: Contributions are welcome. Read the contribution guide, open an issue for any non-trivial change before sending a pull request, and keep the core free of runtime dependencies.
link: Contribution guide | to: https://github.com/fluxgate/fluxgate/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md
link: Code of conduct | to: https://github.com/fluxgate/fluxgate/blob/main/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md
- Fork and branch from main; one logical change per pull request.
- Add or update tests; the suite must pass under `npm test` with no skips.
- Run `npm run lint` and `fluxgate validate` on any example policy you touch.

quote: Make the limit deterministic and the operator's job becomes boring — which is exactly what you want at 3am. | by: Project maintainers

